  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Philippines Cotabato Earthquake 2019</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On Tuesday 29 October 2019 a series of strong earthquakes struck Tulunan North Cotabato Mindanao. The first earthquake was recorded at 9:04am (local time) at magnitude 6.6 and 7km deep. The second significant earthquake was recorded at 10:42am 6.1 magnitude and 9km deep. As of 7:20pm on 29 October 2019 there had been 129 earthquakes recorded by PHILVOCS. PHILVOCS reports that the strongest intensity was intensity VII (destructive) and damage and aftershocks were expected. The total number of people affected is expected to be 2.69 million.</narrative>
  </description>
